reviews.text: My worst dining experience in Hong Kong (and I tried the rotten eggs the other day). I had to wait 40 minutes for the set lunch menu even though the restaurant was not full. The staff could not speak English, were rude and racist as all the guests around got their orders ahead of us despite arriving later. The food was average and my lunch set came with elements missing. Avoid this place

This place is a waste of time. Every lunch they got Salmon Sushi on their menu. It’s a lie to get customers in. They had it maybe three times out of the 15 times I went there over the last year. Only reason I still bothered going was because I worked in that building. And still it’s a scam.
Food not particularly great but good vibe

reviews.author_name: A T M O S P H Y X
reviews.text: Pricey but worth it. Expect to spend up to HKD1000 for two people and around HKD400 for one. They serve sushi, sashimi, ramen, and a variety of grilled food. As for drinks, they serve a large selection of alcohol such as beer, cocktails and mocktails.

Good ramen with a light bit deep and rich enough taste. 
The decoration is modern and there is a decent size counter and a few tables. The plates edge on the comtemporary side and are simple but elegant.
The negi toro maki or shopped spring onion and fatty tuna hand roll was adequate too.
The service was reasonably fast.

reviews.text: Good for public transportation transit areas.  There are mall with famous brands for tourists & local middle classes.  Well-known supermarket & plenty of restaurants as well as fast-food shops.  Also have theatres provide entertainment for family leisure time.
High end mall, great ambiance and has direct airport bag and boarding pass check inn! Now you can enjoy the city instead of rushing to the airport and roaming around with your luggage.
My only real experience is walking through IFC on my way to and from the ferry. Do appreciate the ac and conveniently located city super.

It’s a well located mall with a good choice of stores and restaurants. The exchange square is a central bus station which is close by. The airport express in town check in is located on the ground level and the train station is located below. The Macau ferry stop is walking distance from here through the bridges as well as the central ferry pier.

Awesome mall. They have everything from ships, movie theaters, to upscale restaurants and more low-key joints. They also have the airport express there which is one of the quickest ways to get to the airport. Definitely great to catch up with friends or bring your guests for a fun afternoon!

reviews.text: ifc is probably one of the best malls in Hong Kong. With the wide variety of food and the even wider variety of clothing, this makes the mall a comfortable and one of the best malls. The train station is also located near the mall for easier access and convenient travel. Would definitely recommend to tourists and travelers.

Huge open shopping mall with plenty of restaurants and great connections throughout Hong Kong be they ferry, train, buses or even the airport express. There are plenty of open areas, including the rooftop area which is reserved for restaurants and bars. The area has a luxury vibe at a corresponding price tag.
Probably one of my favorite malls in the world. You can find here basically anything, from Shake Shack, to cold-pressed juices, clothing stores, Apple, electronics and much more.

Hong Kong is full of places like this. Shopping mall stuffed with expensive brands, an Apple store and a cinema. There is a city super and if you want a decent coffee go to fuel. It also has a music shop with a pretty good selection of new vinyl. Best thing to do here? Buy some beers from city super or nearby marks and Spencers and head up to the Mall roof top garden and watch Kowloon as the sun goes down, or a storm is coming in. Pretty awesome.
Excellent mall, just above the Hong Kong train station. Has excellent options for shopping and food which includes all varieties. Overall excellent place.

reviews.text:
我和女友人一起下班，即興來個快吃的晚餐，在ifc的godiva前面的扶手電梯上兩層轉右就到了。餐廳不大，一眼看清，那是晚上9點左右，有一半空的座位。看到其他客人都有點到拉麵，menu最後一頁就有了，6款拉麵，價錢不貴，由其在ifc。
然後點了一碗寫著推薦的gogyo kagashimiso焦香味噌拉麵($128)，湯底很濃郁，我都喝了大半碗，拉麵小幼，都算彈牙，美味程度是我會回頭，為這個拉麵。
想點的刺身set和拖羅已經sold out，只有油甘魚和鯛魚薄切，自己就喜歡比較清淡些的刺身，但大多數的人都比較喜歡油份多些，所以就點了胡麻油甘魚($168)，大大的5塊，中等肥美，灑上黑白芝麻和脆米，可以卷著青瓜絲來吃，別有一番風味，至於會否回頭就未必，但可以一試。
柚子醬油北海道鐵板燒豬($148)就有點失色，一整塊左右的份量，沒有過熟，又不會很乾，醬汁在最底，要拌勻，有一堆椰菜絲和幾件薯仔，薯仔不夠軟身，不夠入味⋯這碟菜色就有點普通了。
總結明顯可見，最推介的是拉麵，胡麻油甘魚都不錯。

又一餐生日飯~~~黎到公司附近IFC既五行🙂

話說呢個位, 可能風水真係唔多好, 印象中已經換過N手既食肆😂

12點零黎到, 都唔駛點等位🤨都唔知係大家無開工, 定個位真係有啲僻, 係IFC中庭3樓凹咗落去🏗️

舖頭既MENU 好簡單, 午飯係得三張紙, 一張封面有個丼🍚、一張就五彩戰隊色拉麵選🍜、一張就小食單點 (A LA CARTE)🍢

坐左係裏面房間, 枱同枱都有啲窄, 畢竟係寸金呎土既IFC, 你要佢寬敞, 就同你銀包搶; 成間餐廳黑色主調, 印象中上兩手都係咁黑麻麻😎

五行術數既嘢, 我就唔多識喇, 咁就揀個五行款 (通常冠名舖頭名既都有保證), 另外配番個手羽先 (雞翼哦🐥）

等咗一陣, 服務員拿個盤托咗個花樽上黎… 個拉麵碗咁Q大… 入面仲要烏卒卒 (好似好似一隻黑蟋蟀) 啲係湯面浮浮既黑蒜油, 令個碗面既密度由液體轉變成固體一樣 飲起湯頭黎, 有啲似試緊芝士火鍋底既稠密程度, 味道濃厚到無空間去融入其他味道🤤🤤

麵底硬淨係我欣賞既, 加埋濃密既湯底, 有啲似撈麵; 另外肥叉係佢湯底度相得益彰, 將個濃既程度提升到十級; 最後先黎品賞隻半熟蛋, 將啲黑蒜油慢慢湧入去蛋黃中心🍳🍳撈埋一齊黎食, 又幾得意

另外佢既沙律醬雞翼係開咗邊, 啱晒啲要食雞翼又懶咬既人; 沙律醬既酸同個雞翼又MATCH到, 唔錯👍

總體味道中上; 生日唔駛自已埋單, 不過都极到唔係平, 其實唔駛點等位可能同佢個價錢都有關🤑🤑

My worst dining experience in Hong Kong (and I tried the rotten eggs the other day). I had to wait 40 minutes for the set lunch menu even though the restaurant was not full. The staff could not speak English, were rude and racist as all the guests around got their orders ahead of us despite arriving later. The food was average and my lunch set came with elements missing. Avoid this place

This place is a waste of time. Every lunch they got Salmon Sushi on their menu. It’s a lie to get customers in. They had it maybe three times out of the 15 times I went there over the last year. Only reason I still bothered going was because I worked in that building. And still it’s a scam.
